<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12140h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12140h">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12140h"> 140(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">X</font> totem (ass)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The idea of reincarnation is widespread. &hellip; The Huron also believed in reincarnation, for they used to bury the bodies of little children by the roadside, in the hope that they would enter passing women and thus be born. They also possessed a set of names for each clan, all derived from the characteristics of the clan <mark>totem</mark>, from which names the council women of the clan chose one for each child. <small> William James Perry, <a name="ORMR" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ORMR"><cite title="source">Origin of Magic and Religion</cite></a> (1923) 145-6</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c12144d" href="c12all.htm#c12144d">VI.C.12:144(d)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
